narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The course introduces students to the Air Force, customs and courtesies, forms of communication, and the leadership framework.
I learned about the history of the US Air Force and other important Air Force knowledge, the values of the US Air Force, and leadership.
I learned customs and courtesies of the Air Force and the history of the organization's founding.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course was very manageable and the only preparation required was skimming the student readers for the lesson in advance. The course is very interactive and is effective at teaching the objectives required for the first semester of the Air Force ROTC program. Be prepared to go with the flow of the course and rely on your peers for support when it comes to writing the MFR or the career field briefing. Most of the instructions are very laid out, but the course is also highly collaborative in nature. The assignments, in part, feel independent from the course as little class time is used to introduce the assignment. Assignments are very self-explanatory and standardized.
One strength of this course is the speaking opportunities for all students. The course could be improved by requiring students to give two instead of just one presentation.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: The audience of the course if Air Force ROTC cadets; content taught in the course is highly specialized and may not be useful for others not involved or connected to the Air Force. The course lacks intellectual challenge and discussion as the content is very objective and information you need to know.
I would recommend this course to any students in AFROTC.
